Title : Linnédalen
Text : [[File:Nordenskiöld Land IMG 3279 Kongressvatnet Linnéelva.JPG|thumb|right|200 px|From Linnédalen.]]
'''Linnédalen''' is a valley in [[Nordenskiöld Land]] at [[Spitsbergen]], [[Svalbard]]. It is named after Swedish botanist [[Carl Linnaeus]]. The valley has a length of about ten kilometers, and is located east of the mountain  ridge of [[Linnéfjella]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Linnédalen |title=Linnédalen (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> In the lower part of the valley is the lake of [[Linnévatnet]], which is among the largest lakes of Spitsbergen.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Linnévatnet |title=Linnévatnet (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Arctic Pilot: Sailing directions Svalbard&ndash;Jan Mayen |year=1988 | volume =7 |publisher=The Norwegian Hydrographic Service and The Norwegian Polar Institute |location=Stavanger |language= |isbn=82-90653-06-9 |page=220}}  </ref>

